{
  "version": "0.4",
  "title": "XCP Home Part 2 - Parallax & Text Content",
  "type": "page",
  "content": [
    {
      "id": "parallax-section",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Parallax CTA Section",
        "layout": "full_width",
        "content_width": "full",
        "min_height": {"unit": "vh", "size": 100},
        "background_background": "classic",
        "background_image": {"url": "[uc_local]assets/images/triumph-bike-snow.jpg"},
        "background_size": "cover",
        "background_position": "center center",
        "background_attachment": "fixed",
        "background_repeat": "no-repeat",
        "padding": {"unit": "px", "top": "100", "right": "20", "bottom": "100", "left": "20"},
        "content_position": "middle"
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "parallax-content",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 100,
            "content_width": "full"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "parallax-heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Your Authentic Story. Their Undivided Attention.",
                "header_size": "h2",
                "align": "center",
                "typography_font_size": {"unit": "px", "size": 48},
                "typography_font_size_mobile": {"unit": "px", "size": 32},
                "color": "#FFFFFF"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "parallax-text",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p style='text-align: center; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;'>When your visuals truly reflect who you are, your ideal audience feels it. They stop scrolling. They connect. They choose you.</p><p style='text-align: center; font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 800px; margin: 20px auto 0;'><strong>Ready to stand out in a way that feels completely authentic to your brand?</strong></p>",
                "text_color": "#FFFFFF"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "parallax-button",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "button",
              "settings": {
                "text": "Let's Create Your Impact",
                "link": {"url": "#contact-form"},
                "align": "center",
                "size": "lg",
                "button_type": "primary"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "text-content-section",
      "elType": "section",
      "settings": {
        "_title": "Text Content Block",
        "layout": "boxed",
        "content_width": "boxed",
        "padding": {"unit": "px", "top": "80", "right": "20", "bottom": "80", "left": "20"}
      },
      "elements": [
        {
          "id": "text-content-column",
          "elType": "column",
          "settings": {
            "_column_size": 100,
            "content_width": "full"
          },
          "elements": [
            {
              "id": "text-heading",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "heading",
              "settings": {
                "title": "Good Photographs Are Easy. The Right Photograph Is Something Else.",
                "header_size": "h2",
                "align": "center",
                "typography_font_size": {"unit": "px", "size": 40},
                "typography_font_size_mobile": {"unit": "px", "size": 28}
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "text-body",
              "elType": "widget",
              "widgetType": "text-editor",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<div style='max-width: 860px; margin: 0 auto; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.9;'><p>Anyone with a decent camera and a good eye can make a photograph that looks fine. That's not what this is.</p><p>What I do starts well before the shoot — in a real conversation about who you are, who you're trying to reach, and what it is about you that will make those specific people stop mid-scroll and actually pay attention. Not your elevator pitch. The actual thing.</p><p>Then the technical side — 15+ years of knowing exactly what to do with light, timing, and composition — becomes the delivery mechanism for that understanding. The camera is just the tool. The work is everything that happens before and around it.</p><p><strong>The result is imagery with intent behind it.</strong> Images that show the personality of the person, the place, or the thing — not a polished performance of them. Images that resonate with the right people because they were made with those people in mind.</p></div>"
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
